  <% include ../partials/header %>
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="columns is-multiline">
        <div class="column is-12">
          <div>
            <figure class="bg-img">
              <br />
              <br />
              <div class="has-text-centered">
                <h2 class="title is-3">
                  NYT Search
                </h2>
              </div>
              <br />
              <br />
              <br />
            </figure>
          </div>
          <div class="column is-8 is-offset-2">
            <hr />
            <p>
              This is an single page, MERN-stack application that finds articles
              from the New York Times using their search API.
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
              Users can search for a topic and save articles from the results on
              the "search" page. They can also delete articles that have been saved
              from the "saved" page. I enjoy writing straightforward applications
              that do a good job at the task they are developed for!
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
              The app features a Node.js/Express.js backend with a MongoDB/Mongoose
              database (using mLab while deployed on Heroku). I used Axios for in-app
              routing and for calling the NYT API with user-input search terms.
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
              The main purpose of this application was to get comfortable with writing
              in React. Completing the project helped me see the power of React for
              writing frontend code and enabled me to better contribute to other
              applications and team projects.
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
              Use the app <a href="https://stark-caverns-91687.herokuapp.com/">live</a>,
              or check out the <a href="https://github.com/anlawyer/NYT-Article-Search">source code</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
